deck_name: My Witchcrafter Spellbook deck Post Banlist OCT 2022
deck_description:
Witchcrafter, Artificers of magic!!

 

The Witchcrafter archetype is adorable in all artwork that is presented, linking the lore of the spellcaster universe ( Endymion, Spellbook, Invokeds), making a third force to balance power between them. They don't store knowledge like Prophecy-Spellbook or use knowledge for power and war like Endymion, instead they use for (like the name says) craft magic artefacts that which one of the Witchcrafter are responsible for one process (pottery , glass, jewelry, etc). Enough about them, let’s get into the deck.

 

 

 

Main deck Monsters:

 

 

 

3x Witchcrafter Schmietta: every low level Witchcrafter has the effect which she can tribute herself, then discard a spell card to summon any Witchcrafter from the deck. What makes Witchcrafter Schmietta unique is the ability to send any Witchcrafter card, in special Witchcrafter Patronus for crazy combos later on.

 

 

 

3x Witchcrafter Genni: Genni was the “glue” that this deck was lacking.The effect that she banished herself with another Witchcrafter spell card to use this effect again… it’s crazy.

 

 

 

2x Witchcrafter Pittore: Pittore is very risky but with so many Witchcrafter spell cards in theis deck, I think this is enough.

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Potterie: She does absolutely nothing ‘cause Witchcrafter spell cards can recover from the GY by themself, but … man… she is adorable lol.

 

 

 

2x Witchcrafter Golem Aruru: a beefie Hand trap, the ability to bounce any opponent’s monster or recover a Witchcrafter spell card and with 2800 ATK it’s even more juicy.

 

 

 

2x Witchcrafter Haine: Can pop a face up card

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Edel: Edel was more useful in the past, but today with Witchcrafter Unveiling is no longer escential, nevertheless is a good beater.

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Mademe Verre: The favorite snob loli, this little brat it’s an Inferno (i’m cursing in my native language). She can negate a face up monster by discarding a spell card, boost a spellcaster by 1000 ATK for which different spell card in your hand, combos with Spell Chronicle and Witchcrafter Patronus… Now I know why she looks so snobbish in the artwork.

 

 

 

Spell cards

 

 

 

2x Witchcrafter Holiday: Every spell card of this archetype returns for the player hand if weren’t used in this turn, and of course has an additional unique effect.This card is basically a monster reborn for the archetype. 

 

 

 

3x Witchcrafter Unveiling: Special summons any Witchcrafter from your hand, the department that was lacking in this deck. 

 

 

 

3x Witchcrafter Creation: Search any Witchcrafter monster from your deck

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Scroll: Can make you draw a card if your Witchcrafter monster destroys another monster by attack.  

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Collaboration: Makes your monster punch a second time, with Witchcrafter Mademe Verre effect… this is kind of interesting.

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Bystreet: Protects your monster for one destruction.

 

 

 

1x Witchcrafter Draping: a Mystical Space Typhoon on steroids, bouncing any spell/trap card up the number Witchcrafter you control.

 

 

 

2x Spellbook of Judgment: It’s banned for a reason, this card is outrageous, can make you go +4 with the right setup and bring any Spellcaster monster (on in our case, any Witchcrafter monster) up to the number of Spellbooks added to your hand. I hope this card never comes back to the game… that's because it’s so awesome!!

 

 

 

2x Spellbook of Secrets: search any spellbook card.

 

 

 

1x Spellbook of Power: boost the attack of your monster and can search any spellbook card if this monster destroys another monster for battle.

 

 

 

1x Spellbook of Knowledge: a draw card for spellcaster type monster, can even put some GY setup for future plays and a materia folder for Spellbook of Judgment.

 

 

 

1x Spellbook of Wisdom: Protection for you spellcaster and a materia folder for Spellbook of Judgment.

 

 

 

2x Spell Chronicle: This is an honorable Witchcrafter card. The effect that banishes any 5 spell card from your deck, and later can be brought to your hand by the effect of Witchcrafter Patronus and potentially making a 3+ card advantage … is insane. Combos with Witchcrafter Mademe Verre, Witchcrafter Haine, Witchcrafter Edea, just an incredible teck.

 

 

 

Trap cards

 

 

 

2x Witchcrafter Patronus: the effect that matters is the GY one. Banishing itself to add to you handy any Witchcrafter card with different names from your banishment pile… is insane if you consider you are running Spell Chronicle in this deck.

3x Evenly matched: awsome tech tô go second.

 

 

 

Extra Deck

 

 

 

The extra deck is more kind of a tool to deal with the unknown, so I’ll not discuss it. Your main play is on the main deck.

 

 

 

Conclusion

 

A very fun waifu deck , with so many options and so insane plays.. I know that are not a very strong deck … but come on Potterie is so cute. I hope you enjoy it.

deck_excerpt: Pure Tear with emphasis on control
deck_description:
Its Hand-Trap tear. I main 3 Belle because the Bystial guys are in the meta, but you can take those out for whatever you want if you dont like it.

I really like the Rainbow Bridge tech, going +3 off a single FBG or a good mill is awesome (also CB is based), but you can sub it out for the Branded in High Spirits package to achieve similar results. Make sure to take Mine out of the side if you do.

You could probably cut a Kit and the Unicorn for Bahamut + Toad, but I really dont think its consistent enough to include.

Im not playing Ash because its not amazing this format, a single Ash is not going to do much, but if your locals or regionals has a heavy rouge presence then go ahead and play it.

When MAMA comes out I expect this list to stay the same, but obviously every deck in the format is going to get pushed down by Ishizu Tear.

deck_description:
This deck was mainly built around my love for Super Robolady and Super Roboyarou. The Machine King monsters do well since the deck is centered around Machine-type monsters. Power Bond and Limiter Removal work well to boost the Attack of the Machine/Fusion monsters.

Basically, the goal is to summon any of the Fusion monsters possible and use them as beat sticks. Alternatively, try getting as many monsters on the field along with Machine King or Perfect Machine King to boost their Attacks and the use them as beat sticks.

Some other options are in the Extra Deck. Cyber Dragon can be used to with any of the other Machine-type monsters to bring out the Chimeratech monsters.

deck_excerpt: Break the board, not the bank!
deck_description: This is my personal Dragon Link deck. This deck (In my opinion, anyways) is much cheaper than your aveage Dragon Link deck. If you have purchased Rokket Revolt and Albaz Strike, you will have most of the cards required to build this deck. I have chosen to include Stardust and Scarlight as they are extremely flexible in this deck, but any generic level 5, 8 or 11 synchros work as well. I am proud to officially declare this the cheapest Dragon Link deck on ygoprodeck.com, and I hope you enjoy the deck as much as I do! :D

Small World searches a looooot of stuff in this deck. And some very funny things in the side.

 

You can turn your dead Shifters into Martha, and almost every hand trap goes through Droll as a bridge. Against Floo, you can bridge to Necroworld Banshee. Necroface is there because funny haha card against Runic Splights.

Bridges:

Any Exosister -> Dshifter -> Necroworld Banshee/Necroface

Any Exosister -> Dshifter/Droll -> Exosister Martha

Any handtrap (including Ghost Reaper) -> Droll -> Any Exosister

Exosister Sophia -> D.D. Crow -> Necroworld Banshee/Necroface

Ghost Reaper -> D.Shifter -> Necroworld Banshee/Necroface
This is an altergeist deck

deck_excerpt: what i'll be playing to counter the best deck (Cybernetic Revolution Prog Deck)i
deck_description:
if my buddies see this (since prog is on friday ( posted on tuesday nighht)).... uhhhhhh grats. here's my list.

                                                                                                              yeah i know 2 skyscraper. crazy right?

anyway, the main idea here is Jerry beans man

OK i'm kidding a bit, but he sums up the power cards of this format which are as follows:

Earth Art- allows you to toggle between earth monsters, which is pretty dang awesome in a format where you have essentially 3+ Goblin attack forces. I'm only on 2 as it *can* be a bit of a win more card, and thus a dead draw on the backfoot.

Double Attack- also a win-more card but in this case you're winning more by normal summoning Lei Lei and getting in there for 4600. [note: it requires you to discard a higher level monster, which is why jerry beans man (lv 3) works so well.]

Gyroid- he lives through one attack (unless it's a drillroid and gyroid is in def)  [1000/1000 tho]

Steamroid- essentially another 2300 attacker. [but one that jerry can get over]

                   [honorable mention to powerbonding steam gyroid]

-------------------------

moving on to other notables.

Hero signal- pulling guys out of the deck is still very strong. if you're worried about drawing both claymen, go ahead and run some more heros in the main. =D

a Rival appears- everything is level 4. unless it's level 5.

Conscription- WARNING: YOU WILL ALWAYS GIVE YOUR OPPONENT A FREE DRAW AND THEY WILL ALWAYS TAKE YOUR MECHANICAL HOUND

Mechanical Hound - sh*t tier. garbage. don't run it. dead in your hand and it's a free conscription for your enemy.

avian- serchable off signal, level 3 (double attack+ skyscraper |_O>O_| ), also wind art-able

wind art- insane removal, and you're prolly already playing gyroid. bit bricky though. so be careful with ratios.

Rising energy - this is how anything is getting over anything else

Scorpion- crazy

CyDra - crazy

Lei Lei - crazy

Dim Wall - Crazy

I play this a lot in nexus and master duel 
:D

deck_excerpt: Dark World, Danger!, DMT, Domain format
deck_description:
Dark World/Danger! deck for Domain Format, a casual multiplayer free-for-all format inspired by MTG Commander format.

Time to hire Tour Guide From the Underworld and his crew for a trip to the Danger! World. Using her as the Deck Master gives me access to DARK or Fiend monsters.

The idea is use Tour Guide From the Underworld as a toolbox to get an easy search, recycle a monster from the GY or get a Dark World monster into the field for Grapha, Dragon Lord of Dark World or Reign-Beaux, Overking of Dark World.

Muckraker From the Underworld is an amazing card, it gives destruction protection and allows us to target a Fiend monster in our GY, then discard a card to special summon it.

 Tour Guide From the Underworld can special summon this cards from your Deck

  • Sangan: Go for a Link 2 monster to search a monster with 1500 or less ATK from your deck.
  • Tour Bus From the Underworld: Go for a Rank 3 Xyz and detach Tour Bus to recycle a monster in your GY.
  • Doomdog Octhros: Go for a Link 2 monster to search a Lv 8 Fiend monster from your deck.
  • Broww, Huntsman of Dark World: Bounce it to special summon Grapha, Dragon Lord of Dark World  or Reign-Beaux, Overking of Dark World.
  • Dark Spirit of Banishment: Quick GY setup.
  • Dark Spirit of Malice: Quick GY setup.

Notable techs:

  • Diabolica, Dragon Fiend Commander: Helps with Rank 8 Xyz plays and recycle.
  • Zalamander Catalyzer: This card is a free Dark World or Danger discard trigger.
  • Forced Requisition: Destroy your opponent hand.

Cards for further testing:

  • Fabled Raven and Lv 7, 8 and 9 Synchros.
  • The Dark - Hex-Sealed Fusion, Predaplant Triphyoverutum and Starving Venom Fusion Dragon.
  • Other Rank 8, Rank 4 and Rank 3 Xyz like Dingirsu, the Orcust of the Evening Star, Number 68: Sanaphond the Sky Prison, Number 60: Dugares the Timeless or Ghostrick Alucard.
  • Number 84: Pain Gainer and Number 77: The Seven Sins combo.
  • Number 97: Draglubion, Number 92: Heart-eartH Dragon and Number C92: Heart-eartH Chaos Dragon combo.
  • Anti Battle package: Gorz the Emissary of Darkness, Tragoedia and Battle Fader.

We play on Discord often. Anyone can come ask questions or learn the format to build a deck. https://discord.gg/GxXHC4qCYM
